## introduction

<a href="#introduction" id="user-content-introduction" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: introduction"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

`_hyperscript` is a small, open scripting language inspired by <a href="https://hypercard.org/HyperTalk%20Reference%202.4.pdf" rel="nofollow">hypertalk</a>

it is a companion project of <a href="https://htmx.org" rel="nofollow">https://htmx.org</a>

<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto">

## quickstart

<a href="#quickstart" id="user-content-quickstart" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: quickstart"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

<div class="highlight highlight-text-html-basic notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" snippet-clipboard-copy-content="
&lt;script src=&quot;https://unpkg.com/hyperscript.org@0.9.14&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;


&lt;button _=&quot;on click toggle .clicked&quot;&gt;
  Toggle the &quot;clicked&quot; class on me
&lt;/button&gt;


&lt;div _=&quot;on mouseOver toggle mouse-over on #foo&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;button _=&quot;on click call aJavascriptFunction() then
           wait 10s then
           call anotherJavascriptFunction()&quot;&gt;
           Do some stuff
&lt;/button&gt;">

    <script src="https://unpkg.com/hyperscript.org@0.9.14"></script>


    <button _="on click toggle .clicked">
      Toggle the "clicked" class on me
    </button>


    <div _="on mouseOver toggle mouse-over on #foo">
    </div>

    <button _="on click call aJavascriptFunction() then
               wait 10s then
               call anotherJavascriptFunction()">
               Do some stuff
    </button>

</div>

## contributing

<a href="#contributing" id="user-content-contributing" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: contributing"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="octicon octicon-link" /></a>

</div>

- please include test cases in [`/test`](https://github.com/bigskysoftware/_hyperscript/tree/dev/test) and docs in [`/www`](https://github.com/bigskysoftware/_hyperscript/tree/dev/www)
  - you can run the test suite by viewing `test/index.html` in a browser.
- development pull requests should be against the `dev` branch, docs fixes can be made directly against `master`
- you can build \_hyperscript as shown: `npm run dist`. building is not necessary during development to run tests.
